13/07/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- A four-day military exercise that included 750 troops from Albania, Italy and Macedonia ended Friday (11 July). 
Air, ground and naval forces participated in the drill, aimed at improving trilateral military co-operation and boosting joint activities of the Albanian and Macedonian Armies within the framework of preparations for NATO membership. 
(Albanian TV, BBC, MIA, A1 TV - 11/07/03)
